HEADWORD: Hydrosalt
<hw>Hy"dro*salt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>salt</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A salt supposed to be formed by a hydracid and a
base.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An acid salt.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>A hydrous salt; a salt combined with water of
hydration or crystallization.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

